":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12421675/comment/12694138","id":"12694138","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Consider the following simple scenario:\n* Generate data\n * Datanodes in a given rack goes down(2 replicas of many block are lost)\n* Run sort on the generated data\n* Sort job fails\n* The filesystem is declared CORRUPT\n\nHowever the expected behavior would be to successfully sort the data available using the third replica of blocks.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-03-31T14:53:07.119+0000","updated":"2009-03-31T14:53:07.119+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12421675/comment/12694147","id":"12694147","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=nidaley","name":"nidaley","key":"nidaley","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Nigel Daley","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Does your randomwriter.cfg lower the default replication from 3 to 2 or 1?  Or does the randomwriter code?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=nidaley","name":"nidaley","key":"nidaley","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Nigel Daley","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-03-31T15:20:52.471+0000","updated":"2009-03-31T15:20:52.471+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12421675/comment/12694157","id":"12694157","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"bq. Does your randomwriter.cfg lower the default replication from 3 to 2 or 1? Or does the randomwriter code?\nNone of the above two scenarios occur.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId