:"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=iyappans","name":"iyappans","key":"iyappans","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Iyappan Srinivasan","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-04-03T08:22:52.432+0000","updated":"2009-04-03T08:22:52.432+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12421675/comment/12695292","id":"12695292","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=iyappans","name":"iyappans","key":"iyappans","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Iyappan Srinivasan","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"I was able to reproduce the above said issue.\n\n1) In the cluster, generate data using randomwriter\n2) Get one rack and kill all the datanodes in that rack only.\n3) Run sort job. It fails.\n4) Run Fsck from root. It says data corrupt.\n\nI have attached the logs of these .","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=iyappans","name":"iyappans","key":"iyappans","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Iyappan Srinivasan","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-04-03T08:27:50.565+0000","updated":"2009-04-03T08:27:50.565+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12421675/comment/12696299","id":"12696299","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=owen.omalley","name":"owen.omalley","key":"owen.omalley","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=owen.omalley&avatarId=29697","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=owen.omalley&avatarId=29697","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=owen.omalley&avatarId=29697","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=owen.omalley&avatarId=29697"},"displayName":"Owen O'Malley","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Did you have the topology defined? If not, there is nothing DFS can do. If so, the question becomes why blocks ended up with all the replicas on one rack.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=owen.omalley","name":"owen.omalley","key":"owen.omalley","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=owen.omalley&avatarId=29697","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=owen.omalley&avatarId=29697","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=owen.omalley&avatarId=29697","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=owen.omalley&avatarId=29697"},"displayName":"Owen O'Malley","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2009-04-06T23:44:03.778+0000","updated":"2009-04-06T23:44:03.778+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12421675/comment/12696387","id":"12696387","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avata